# Kubernetes Conventions

- All K8S manifests live in `K8S/` at the repo root
- Each service gets a Deployment + ClusterIP Service in one file: `<service>-depl.yml`
- Docker images are pushed to `ctrlal/<service-name>:latest`
- Services expose port 80 mapped to container targetPort 8080
- The shared PostgreSQL instance is at `pssql-depl-clusterip-srv:5432`
- Each service uses a separate database on the shared PostgreSQL
- Ingress routes are defined in `ingress-srv.yml` under host `acme.com`
- After adding a new service, always add its route to the ingress
